<HEAD>Mrs. Baker Has Malignant Growth Removed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Joy Baker, wife of former Senate Republican
Leader Howard H. Baker Jr., has had a small malignant growth
removed from her right lung.
   The tumor was removed Wednesday during a 90-minute operation by
Mayo Clinic doctors at St. Marys Hospital in Rochester, Minn., said
spokesman Tom Griscom.
   A source familiar with her case, who did not wish to be
identified by name, said the growth was ``a low grade tumor'' not a
recurrence of the cancer that was removed from the same lung in
1982.
   She is not expected to require additional treatment, the source
said.
   Mrs. Baker is the daughter of the late Senate Republican leader
Everett Dirksen of Illinois. Howard Baker served in the Senate from
1966 until 1984 and was President Reagan's White House chief of
staff from February 1987 until July 1988.
   The Bakers' primary residence is in Huntsville, Tenn., but they
also maintain a home in Washington, where Baker practices law.
</TEXT>
